    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with\u00a01 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong>\u00a0over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-pea-leek-and-bacon-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the bacon is browning, chop your <strong>leek[s] </strong>in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-pea-leek-and-bacon-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon is crisp, add the<strong>\u00a0sliced leek</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-pea-leek-and-bacon-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has started to soften, add your <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 2 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-pea-leek-and-bacon-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>\u00a0in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Stir the<strong> chicken stock</strong> into the rice\u00a0and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> rice mixture</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>rice mixture</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>(or casserole dish!)</p><p>Put the dish in the oven\u00a0for an initial 20 min or until the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked</strong> <strong>risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-pea-leek-and-bacon-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the baked risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven</p><p>Stir in your<strong> blanched peas</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven for 5 min to warm through</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a small pinch of<strong> salt</strong> in a small bowl<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-pea-leek-and-bacon-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once warmed through, remove from the oven and stir through your <strong>grated</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>oven baked pea, leek & bacon risotto</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/oven-baked-pea-leek-and-bacon-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve\u00a0the <strong>oven baked pea, leek & bacon risotto</strong></p><p>Top with a handful of <strong>salad </strong>and drizzle over the <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> if needed</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
